reviews.text:
I used to go there for the veggie burger but since I learnt to cook up a crackling burger myself I seldom go there. 
Anyways it's good okay good but look out for the discounts on eatigo which then makes it more worthwhile

Ordered an impossible burger and an original burger to compare. Honestly, the impossible burger is more juicy while the original burger is a bit over cooked. Both photos are impossible burger. Can taste strong bean flavour which I’m ok with but there’s controversial genetic engineered heme in it according to some media...
A really quick lunch in 10. The fries were not good. That’s a 85 set

The food is very good.
And Not to expensive.
As possible as I want to have again.
We love the taste of their burgers, fries and their freshly-made milkshakes
